South Africa&rsquo;s power system has progressed to a position of surplus capacity&sbquo; opening opportunities to extend regional interconnections and to accommodate a changing power generation mix to grow the country&rsquo;s economy&sbquo; Eskom said on Saturday.The electricity parastal said it had committed itself to continue its investment in transmission infrastructure and to leverage advanced technology solutions for a reliable and sustainable power grid."Managing the largest capacity expansion project in Africa&sbquo; Eskom has invested approximately R12 billon in transmission infrastructure and strengthening projects since 2014 to the end of September 2016. More than 6&sbquo;000 km of transmission lines and 32&sbquo;000 MVA of substation transformer capacity has been installed since 2005&sbquo;" the power provider said.TMG Digital